                                </foliation>
                                <collation>
                                    <formula>1-5(10), 6(1+10), 7-9(8), 10(1+1+1+4), 11(12+1)</formula>
                                    <p>
                                        <ref target="https://vceditor.library.upenn.edu/project/69ce52206e6f4a0001f9744e/viewOnly">VisColl collation</ref>. Structure of quire 10 tentative, most likely it originally conisted of 8 leaves, but three of the remaining leaves are today almost detached. Parchment guards at the centre of each quire, and between first and second quire.</p>
