                            <handDesc>
                                <p/>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-4">
                                    <locus from="93r" to="105v" scheme="folios"/>Gothic cursive. The text on these leaves varies a great deal in terms of ink and the size of the script. It may be written by several different hands, but it is also possible that it is the same scribe using different pens. </handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="93r" to="105v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Additions in the margins by at least two different contemporary hands. The additions consist of corrections, phrases such as <quote>Nota bene</quote> on <locus from="93v" to="93v" scheme="folios"/>, and comments on the state of the text, e.g. <locus from="94v" to="94v" scheme="folios"/>, bottom margin: <quote>hic ulla/-us deficit</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink, capitals touched in red, rubrics underlined in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="93r" to="96r" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 2-3 lines in red.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="98r" to="105r" scheme="folios"/>: space reserved for initials, often with guide letters.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="bookmarks">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="93" to="93" scheme="folios"/>: bookmarks in red paper glued to the page.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
